{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Parmesan, cayenne pepper, rosemary, thyme, garlic powder, oregano and bay leaf in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place water and yeast in mixing bowl then heat <nobr>1 min\/37°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, grease a large bowl.","Add flour, salt and reserved cheese and herb mix then knead <nobr>1 min 30 sec\/<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared bowl, cover and leave to rise in a warm place for approx. 40 minutes. Scrape down dough inside bowl with spatula then set aside in fridge for 4 hours.","Towards the end of this time, preheat oven to 200°C and line a baking tray with baking paper.","Divide rested dough into five portions and roll in semolina. Using a pasta machine, roll dough out thinly. Cut each piece into thin strips (approx. 5 mm) using a tagliatelle cutter or long sharp knife. Arrange strips on prepared baking tray, sprinkle with olive oil and sea salt. Bake for 8-10 minutes (200°C) until golden brown.","Cool on a wire rack before serving or store in an airtight container until needed."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["20 g Parmesan cheese, cut in pieces (2 cm)","1 pinch ground cayenne pepper","½ tsp fresh rosemary leaves","½ tsp fresh thyme leaves","½ tsp garlic powder","1 tsp dried oregano","1 bay leaf","240 g water","15 g fresh yeast","olive oil, for greasing and sprinkling","350 g strong white bread flour","1 tsp fine sea salt, plus extra for sprinkling","semolina, for sprinkling"]}],"id":"r130515","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-rpoBDa6OnDU\/XZanFYLPFRI\/AAAAAAAAg54\/QYmgJKqEjQsx-lPLUfVpxDybrFYWfa3iQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1ixh54Sa0w48ncj9.png","title":"Grissini with Parmesan and Herbs","publishedAt":"2016-12-12T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"44 g","calories":"1041 kJ \/ 249 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, large bowl, baking tray and paper, long sharp knife, rol